obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (21256)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605&sectionId=21256&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Marine Products Export`
  line `Development Authority Act, 1972.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint:`
  line
  line `Provided that different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 12th July, 1972, vide notification No. G.S.R. 388(E), dated 12th July, 1972, in respect of the provisions of sections other`
  line `than sections 11 to 19 (both inclusive), see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(i).`
  line
  line `15th January, 1973, vide notification No. G.S.R. 8(E), dated 10th January, 1973, in respect of the provisions of`
  line `sections 11 to 19 (both inclusive), see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(i).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (21257)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Declaration as to expediency of control by the Union.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605&sectionId=21257&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `It is hereby declared that it is expedient`
  line `in the public interest that the Union should take under its control the marine products industry.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (21258)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605&sectionId=21258&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Authority" means the Marine Products Export Development Authority established under`
  line `section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) "Chairman" means the Chairman of the Authority;`
  line
  line `(c) "conveyance" includes a carrier vessel or a vehicle;`
  line
  line `(d) "dealer" means a dealer in any of the marine products;`
  line
  line `(e) "Director" means the Director of Marine Products Export Development appointed under`
  line `section 7;`
  line
  line `(f) "export and import" mean respectively taking out of, or bringing into, India by land, sea`
  line `or air;`
  line
  line `(g) "fishing vessel" means a ship or boat fitted with mechanical means of propulsion which is`
  line `exclusively engaged in sea-fishing for profit;`
  line
  line `(h) "marine products" includes all varieties of fishery products known commercially as shrimp,`
  line `prawn, lobster, crab, fish, shell-fish, other aquatic animals or plants or part thereof and any other`
  line `products which the Authority may, by notification in the Gazette of India, declare to be marine`
  line `products for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(i) "member" means a member of the Authority;`
  line
  line `(j) "owner", in relation to any fishing vessel or in relation to any processing plant or storage`
  line `premises for marine products or in relation to any conveyance used for the transport of marine`
  line `products, includes`
  line
  line `(i) any agent of the owner; and`
  line
  line `(ii) a mortgagee, lessee or other person in actual possession of the fishing vessel, processing`
  line `plant, storage premises or conveyance;`
  line
  line `(k) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(l) "processing", in relation to marine products, includes the preservation of such products such as`
  line `canning, freezing, drying, salting, smoking, peeling or filleting and any other method of processing`
  line `which the Authority may, by notification in the Gazette of India, specify in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (21259)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Establishment and constitution of the Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605&sectionId=21259&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf, there shall be established`
  line `for the purposes of this Act, an Authority to be called the Marine Products Export Development`
  line Authority.
  line
  line `(2) The Authority shall be a body corporate by the name aforesaid, having perpetual succession and a`
  line `common seal, with power to acquire, hold and dispose of property, both movable and immovable, and to`
  line `contract, and shall by the said name sue and be sued.`
  line
  line `(3) The Authority shall consist of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairman to be appointed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) the Director of Marine Products Export Development, ex-officio;`
  line
  line `(c) three members of Parliament of whom two shall be elected by the House of the People and`
  line `one by the Council of States;`
  line
  line `(d) five members to represent respectively the Ministries of the Central Government dealing`
  line with
  line
  line `(i) agriculture,`
  line
  line `(ii) finance,`
  line
  line `(iii) foreign trade,`
  line
  line `(iv) industry, and`
  line
  line `(v) shipping and transport;`
  line
  line `(e) such number of other members not exceeding twenty as the Central Government may think`
  line `expedient, to be appointed by that Government by notification in the Official Gazette from among`
  line `persons who are in its opinion capable of representing--`
  line
  line `(i) the Governments of the States or Union territories having a sea-coast;`
  line
  line `(ii) the interests of owners of fishing vessels, processing plants or storage premises for marine`
  line `products and conveyances used for the transport of marine products;`
  line
  line `(iii) the interests of dealers;`
  line
  line `(iv) the interests of persons employed in the marine products industry;`
  line
  line `(v) the interests of persons employed in research institutions engaged in the researches`
  line `connected with the said industry; and`
  line
  line `(vi) such other persons or class of persons who, in the opinion of the Central Government,`
  line `ought to be represented on the Authority.`
  line
  line `(4) The number of persons to be appointed as members from each of the categories specified in`
  line `clause (e) of sub-section (3), the term of office of the members other than the member referred to in`
  line `clause (b) of that sub-section, and the manner of filling vacancies among, and the procedure to be`
  line `followed in the discharge of their functions by the members shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) Any officer of the Central Government, not being a member of the Authority, when deputed by`
  line `that Government in this behalf, shall have the right to attend meetings of the Authority and take part in the`
  line `proceedings thereof but shall not be entitled to vote.`
  line
  line `(6) The Authority shall elect from among its members a Vice-Chairman who shall exercise such of`
  line `the powers and perform such of the functions of the Chairman as may be prescribed or as may be`
  line `delegated to him by the Chairman.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (21260)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Acts or proceedings of Authority or its Committees not to be invalidated.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605&sectionId=21260&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `No act or`
  line `proceeding of the Authority or any Committee appointed by it under section 8, shall be invalidated merely`
  line `by reason of--`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the Authority or such Committee; or`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the appointment of a person acting as a member of the Authority or such`
  line `Committee; or`
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in the procedure of the Authority or such Committee not affecting the merits`
  line `of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (21261)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Salary and allowances of Chairman.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605&sectionId=21261&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The Chairman shall be entitled to such salary and`
  line `allowances and such conditions of service in respect of leave, pension, provident fund and other matters`
  line `as may, from time to time, be fixed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (21262)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Executive officers of the Authority and other staff.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605&sectionId=21262&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall appoint`
  line `a Director of Marine Products Export Development to exercise such powers and perform such duties`
  line `under the Chairman as may be prescribed or as may be delegated to him by the Chairman.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall appoint a Secretary to the Authority to exercise such powers and`
  line `perform such duties under the Chairman as may be prescribed or as may be delegated to him by the`
  line Chairman.
  line
  line `(3) The Director and the Secretary to the Authority shall be entitled to such salaries and allowances`
  line `and such conditions of service in respect of leave, pension, provident fund and other matters as may be`
  line `fixed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to such control and restrictions as may be prescribed, the Authority may appoint such`
  line `other officers and employees as may be necessary for the efficient performance of its functions and pay`
  line `them such salaries and allowances as it may determine from time to time.`
  line
  line `(5) The Chairman, the Director, the Secretary and other employees of the Authority shall not`
  line `undertake any work unconnected with their duties under this Act except with the permission of the`
  line `Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (21263)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Committees of the Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605&sectionId=21263&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority may appoint such Committees as may be`
  line `necessary for the efficient discharge of its duties and performance of its functions under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Authority shall have the power to co-opt as members of any Committee appointed under`
  line `sub-section (1) such other number of persons who are not members of the Authority, as it may think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (21264)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Functions of the Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605&sectionId=21264&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the duty of the Authority to promote, by such`
  line `measures as it thinks fit, the development under the control of the Central Government of the marine`
  line `products industry with special reference to exports.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of sub-section (1), the measures referred to`
  line `therein may provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) developing and regulating off-shore and deep-sea fishing and undertaking measures for the`
  line `conservation and management of off-shore and deep-sea fisheries;`
  line
  line `(b) registering fishing vessels, processing plants or storage premises for marine products and`
  line `conveyances used for the transport of marine products;`
  line
  line `(c) fixing of standards and specifications for marine products for purposes of export;`
  line
  line `(d) rendering of financial or other assistance to owners of fishing vessels engaged in off-shore`
  line `and deep-sea fishing and owners of processing plants or storage premises for marine products and`
  line `conveyances used for the transport of marine products, and acting as an agency for such relief and subsidy schemes as may be entrusted to the Authority;`
  line
  line `(e) carrying out inspection of marine products in any fishing vessel, processing plant, storage`
  line `premises, conveyance or other place where such products are kept or handled, for the purpose of`
  line `ensuring the quality of such products;`
  line
  line `(f) regulating the export of marine products;`
  line
  line `(g) improving the marketing of marine products outside India;`
  line
  line `(h) registering of exporters of marine products on payment of such fees as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(i) collecting statistics from persons engaged in the catching of fish or other marine products,`
  line `owners of processing plants or storage premises for marine products or conveyances used for the`
  line `transport of marine products, exporters of such products and such other persons as may be prescribed`
  line `on any matter relating to the marine products industry and the publishing of statistics so collected, or`
  line `portions thereof or extracts therefrom;`
  line
  line `(j) training in various aspects of the marine products industry; and`
  line
  line `(k) such other matters as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The Authority shall perform its functions under this section in accordance with and subject to such`
  line `rules as may be made by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (21265)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Dissolution of the Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605&sectionId=21265&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette and for reasons to be specified therein, direct that the Authority shall be dissolved from such date`
  line `and for such period as may be specified in the notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that before issuing any such notification, the Central Government shall give a reasonable`
  line `opportunity to the Authority to make representations against the proposed dissolution and shall consider`
  line `the representations, if any, of the Authority.`
  line
  line `(2) When the Authority is dissolved under the provisions of sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(a) all members notwithstanding that their term of office has not expired, shall, from the date of`
  line `dissolution, vacate their offices as such members;`
  line
  line `(b) all powers and duties of the Authority shall, during the period of dissolution, be exercised and`
  line `performed by such person or persons as the Central Government may appoint in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(c) all funds and other property vested in the Authority shall, during the period of dissolution, vest`
  line `in the Central Government; and`
  line
  line `(d) as soon as the period of dissolution expires, the Authority shall be reconstituted in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (21266)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Registration of fishing vessel, processing plant, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605&sectionId=21266&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every owner of a fishing vessel,`
  line `processing plant or storage premises for marine products or conveyance used for the transport of marine`
  line `products shall, before the expiration of one month from the date on which he first became owner of such`
  line `fishing vessel, processing plant, storage premises or conveyance, or before the expiration of three months`
  line `from the date of coming into force of this section, whichever is later, apply to the Authority for`
  line `registration under this Act of every such fishing vessel, processing plant, storage premises, or conveyance`
  line `owned by him:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Authority may, for sufficient reason, extend the time-limit for registration by such`
  line `period as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2) Registration once made shall continue to be in force until it is cancelled by the Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (21267)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Application, cancellation, fee payable and other matters relating to registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605&sectionId=21267&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The form`
  line `of application for registration under section 11 and for the cancellation of such registration, the fee`
  line `payable on such applications, the particulars to be included in such applications, the procedure to be`
  line `followed in granting and cancelling registration and the registers to be kept by the Authority shall be such`
  line `as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (21268)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Returns to be made by owners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605&sectionId=21268&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every owner referred to in sub-section (1) of section 11`
  line `shall furnish to the Authority at the prescribed time and in the prescribed manner such returns as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(2) The Authority may authorise a member or any of its officers to inspect any fishing vessel,`
  line `processing plant, storage premises or conveyance at any time to verify the accuracy of any return made`
  line `under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (21269)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title [Repealed.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605&sectionId=21269&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `[Imposition of a cess on marine products exported.] Rep. by the Repealing and Amending`
  line `Act, 2006 (24 of 2006), s. 2 and the First Schedule (w.e.f. 1-6-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (21270)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title [Repealed.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605&sectionId=21270&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `[Payment of proceeds of cess to the Authority.] Rep. by the Repealing and Amending Act, s. 2 and`
  line `the First Schedule ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (21271)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Grants and loans by the Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605&sectionId=21271&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, after due`
  line `appropriation made by Parliament by law in this behalf, pay to the Authority by way of grants or loans`
  line `such sums of money as the Central Government may consider necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (21272)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Constitution of the Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605&sectionId=21272&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be formed a Fund to be called the Marine Products`
  line `Export Development Fund and there shall be credited thereto--`
  line
  line `(a) the proceeds of the cess made over to the Authority by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) all fees levied and collected in respect of registration made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) any other fee that may be levied and collected by the Authority under this Act or the rules`
  line `made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(d) any grants or loans that may be made by the Central Government for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) any grants or loans that may be made by any institution for the purposes of this Act; and`
  line
  line `(f) all sums realised by the Authority in carrying out the measures referred to in section 9.`
  line
  line `(2) The Fund shall be applied--`
  line
  line `(a) for meeting the salaries, allowances and other remuneration of the officers and other`
  line `employees of the Authority;`
  line
  line `(b) for meeting the other administrative expenses of the Authority;`
  line
  line `(c) for meeting the cost of the measures referred to in section 9; and`
  line
  line `(d) for repayment of any loans from the Central Government or from any institution.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (21273)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Borrowing powers of the Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605&sectionId=21273&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Subject to such rules as may be made in this behalf, the`
  line `Authority shall have power to borrow on the security of the Marine Products Export Development Fund`
  line `or any other asset for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (21274)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605&sectionId=21274&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority shall maintain proper accounts and other relevant`
  line `records and prepare an annual statement of accounts, including the profit and loss account and the`
  line `balance-sheet in such form as may be prescribed by the Central Government in consultation with the`
  line `Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Authority shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India at`
  line `such intervals as may be specified by him and any expenditure incurred in connection with such audit`
  line `shall be payable by the Authority to the Comptroller and Auditor-General.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any person appointed by him in connection`
  line `with the audit of the accounts of the Authority shall have the same rights and privileges and authority in`
  line `connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General has in connection with the audit of`
  line `Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the right to demand the production of books, accounts,`
  line `connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect any of the offices of the Authority.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Authority as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or any`
  line `other person appointed by him in this behalf together with the audit report thereon shall be forwarded`
  line `annually to the Central Government and that Government shall cause the same to be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (21275)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Power to prohibit or control imports and exports of marine products.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule for certain words (w.e.f. 16-8-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605&sectionId=21275&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central`
  line `Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make provision for prohibiting, restricting`
  line `or otherwise controlling the import or export of marine products, either generally or in specified classes of`
  line cases.
  line
  line `(2) All marine products to which any order under sub-section (1) applies, shall be deemed to be`
  line `goods of which the import or export has been prohibited under section 11 of the Customs`
  line `Act, 1962 (52 of 1962), and all the provisions of that Act shall have effect accordingly.`
  line
  line `(3) If any person contravenes any order made under sub-section (1), he shall, without prejudice to any`
  line `confiscation or penalty to which he may be liable under the provisions of the Customs Act, 1962 (52`
  line `of 1962), as applied by sub-section (2), ^1[be liable to penalty not less than ten thousand rupees or not`
  line `exceeding twice the value of goods, whichever is higher, in respect of which such order has been made].`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (21276)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Directions by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605&sectionId=21276&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The Authority shall carry out such directions as may be`
  line `issued to it from time to time by the Central Government for the efficient administration of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (21277)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Returns and reports.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605&sectionId=21277&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority shall furnish to the Central Government, at such time`
  line `and in such form and manner as may be prescribed or as the Central Government may direct, such returns`
  line `and statements and such particulars in regard to any proposed or existing programme for the promotion`
  line `and development of the marine products industry, as the Central Government may, from time to time,`
  line require.
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), the Authority shall, as soon as possible`
  line `after the end of each financial year, submit to the Central Government a report in such form and before`
  line `such date, as may be prescribed, giving a true and full account of its activities, policy and programmes`
  line `during the previous financial year.`
  line
  line `(3) A copy of the report received under sub-section (2) shall be laid before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (21278)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Penalty for making false returns.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule, for certain words (w.e.f. 16-8-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605&sectionId=21278&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `Any person who being required by or under this Act to furnish`
  line `any return fails to furnish such return or furnishes a return containing any particular which is false and`
  line `which he knows to be false or does not believe to be true shall ^1[be liable to penalty which may extend to ten`
  line `thousand rupees].`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (21279)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Penalties for obstructing a member or officer of the Authority in the discharge of his duties and for failure to produce books and records.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule, for sections 24 and 25 (w.e.f. 16-8-2024)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605&sectionId=21279&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `^1[24. Penalties for obstructing a member or officer of the Authority in the discharge of his duties and for failure to produce books and records.--Any person who--`
  line
  line `(a) obstructs any member authorised by the Chairman in writing or any officer or other employee of the`
  line `Authority authorised by it in this behalf or any person authorised in this behalf by the Central Government`
  line `or by the Authority, in the exercise of any power conferred, or in the discharge of any duty imposed, on him`
  line `by or under this Act, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or`
  line `with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees, or with both;`
  line
  line `(b) having control over or custody of any account book or other record, fails to produce such book or record when required to do so by or under this Act, shall be liable to penalty which may extend to ten thousand rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (21280)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Other penalties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule, for sections 24 and 25 (w.e.f. 16-8-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605&sectionId=21280&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `[25. Other penalties.-- Whoever contravenes or attempts to contravene or abets the contravention of the`
  line `provisions of this Act or of any rules made thereunder other than the provisions, punishment or penalty for the contravention whereof has been provided for in sections 20, 23 and 24 shall be liable to penalty not less`
  line `than ten thousand rupees, or not exceeding an amount equivalent to the value of goods, whichever is higher,`
  line `in respect of which such contravention has been made, and in case of a continuing contravention as`
  line `aforesaid, a penalty of not less than fifty thousand rupees, or not exceeding an amount equivalent to twice`
  line `the value of goods, whichever is higher, in respect of which such contravention has been made].`
obj_root_law_sections_25_a:
  sectionId (92540)
  sectionNo 25A
  orderNo 26
  title `Adjudication of penalties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule, for sections 24 and 25 (w.e.f. 16-8-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605&sectionId=92540&sectionno=25A&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605
obj_root_law_sections_25_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[25A. Adjudication of penalties.--(1) For the purposes of adjudging penalties under sub-section (3) of section 20, section 23, clause (b) of section 24 and section 25, the Chairman shall appoint the Secretary to the Authority or any other officer authorised by the Central Government, as the case may be, to be an adjudicating officer for holding an inquiry and imposing penalty under the provisions of this Act, in the manner as may be prescribed, after giving the person concerned a reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever is aggrieved by an order of the adjudicating officer may prefer an appeal to the Chairman,`
  line `within a period of sixty days from the date of receipt of such order in such form and manner as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(3) An appeal may be admitted after the expiry of the period of sixty days if the appellant satisfies the`
  line `Chairman that he had sufficient cause for not preferring the appeal within that period.`
  line
  line `(4) No appeal shall be disposed of unless the appellant has been given a reasonable opportunity of being`
  line heard.
  line
  line `(5) The appellate authority referred to in sub-section (2) shall dispose of the appeal within sixty days`
  line `from the date of filing.`
  line
  line `(6) The amount of penalty imposed under sub-section (1), if not paid, shall be recovered as an arrear of`
  line `land revenue.]`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (21281)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 27
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605&sectionId=21281&sectionno=26&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who at the time the offence was committed was in charge of and was responsible`
  line `to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company as well as the company shall be deemed`
  line `to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he exercised all`
  line `due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty`
  line `of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals; and`
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (21282)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 28
  title `Jurisdiction of court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605&sectionId=21282&sectionno=27&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `No court inferior to that of a Presidency magistrate or a Magistrate of the`
  line `first class shall try any offence punishable under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (21283)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 29
  title `Previous sanction of Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605&sectionId=21283&sectionno=28&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `No prosecution for any offence punishable under`
  line `this Act shall be instituted except with the previous sanction of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (21284)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 30
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605&sectionId=21284&sectionno=29&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceedings shall`
  line `lie against the Government, or the Authority or any Committee appointed by it, or any member of the`
  line `Authority or such Committee, or any officer or other employee of the Government or of the Authority or`
  line `any other person authorised by the Government or the Authority, for anything which is in good faith done`
  line `or intended to be done under this Act or the rules made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (21285)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 31
  title `Power to delegate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605&sectionId=21285&sectionno=30&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by order notified in the Official Gazette,`
  line `direct that any power exercisable by it under this Act (not being the power to make rules under`
  line `section 33) may also be exercised, in such cases and subject to such conditions, if any, as may be`
  line `specified in the order, by such officer or authority as may be specified therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (21286)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 32
  title `Suspension of operation of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605&sectionId=21286&sectionno=31&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Central Government is satisfied that circumstances`
  line `have arisen rendering it necessary that certain of the restrictions imposed by this Act should cease to be`
  line `imposed or if it considers necessary or expedient so to do in the public interest, the Central Government`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, suspend or relax to a specified extent, either indefinitely or`
  line `for such period as may be specified in the notification, the operation of all or any of the provisions of this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(2) Where the operation of any provision of this Act has under sub-section (1) been suspended or`
  line `relaxed indefinitely, such suspension or relaxation may at any time while this Act remains in force be`
  line `removed by the Central Government by notification in the Official Gazette.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (21287)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 33
  title `Application of other laws not barred.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605&sectionId=21287&sectionno=32&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall be in addition to and`
  line `not in derogation of the provisions of any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (21288)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 34
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule (w.e.f. 16-8-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605&sectionId=21288&sectionno=33&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the number of persons to be appointed as members from each of the categories specified in`
  line `clause (e) of sub-section (3) of section 4, the term of office and other conditions of service of`
  line `members, the manner of filling vacancies among, and the procedure to be followed in the discharge of`
  line `their functions by, such members;`
  line
  line `(b) the circumstances in which and the authority by which a member may be removed;`
  line
  line `(c) the holding of a minimum number of meetings of the Authority every year;`
  line
  line `(d) the procedure to be followed at meetings of the Authority for the conduct of business and the`
  line `number of members which shall form a quorum at a meeting;`
  line
  line `(e) the maintenance by the Authority of records of business transacted by the Authority and the`
  line `submission of copies thereof to the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(f) the powers of the Authority, its Chairman, the Director and Committees of the Authority with`
  line `respect to the incurring of expenditure;`
  line
  line `(g) the conditions subject to which the Authority may incur expenditure outside India;`
  line
  line `(h) the preparation of budget estimates of receipts and expenditure of the Authority and the`
  line `authority by which the estimates are to be sanctioned;`
  line
  line `(i) the form and manner in which the accounts should be kept by the Authority;`
  line
  line `(j) the deposit of the funds of the Authority in banks and the investment of such funds;`
  line
  line `(k) the conditions subject to which the Authority may borrow;`
  line
  line `(l) the conditions subject to which and the manner in which contracts may be entered into by or`
  line `on behalf of the Authority;`
  line
  line `(m) the additional matters in respect of which the Authority may undertake measures in the`
  line `discharge of its functions;`
  line
  line `(n) the remuneration and other allowances payable to the person or persons referred to in`
  line `clause (b) of sub-section (2) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(o) the form of, and the particulars to be contained in, any returns or reports to be made to the`
  line `Authority under this Act;`
  line
  line `(p) the form of, and the manner of making applications for registration and for its cancellation by`
  line `the Authority, the fee payable on such applications and the procedure to be followed in granting and`
  line `cancelling registration and the conditions governing such registration;`
  line
  line `(q) the collection of any information or statistics in respect of marine products;`
  line
  line `^1[(qa) the manner of holding inquiry and imposing penalty under sub-section (1) of section 25A;`
  line
  line `(qb) the form and manner of preferring appeal under sub-section (2) of section 25A;]`
  line
  line `(r) any other matter which is to be or may be prescribed by, or provided for by rules under, this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be, after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (21289)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 35
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605&sectionId=21289&sectionno=34&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00001_197213_1517807321605
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority may make regulations not inconsistent with this`
  line `Act and the rules made thereunder for enabling it to discharge its functions under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may provide for all or`
  line `any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the procedure to be followed at meetings of the Committees appointed by the Authority and`
  line `the number of members which shall form a quorum at a meeting;`
  line
  line `(b) the delegation to the Chairman, members, Director, Secretary or other officers of the`
  line `Authority of any of the powers and duties of the Authority under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) the travelling and other allowances of members of the Authority and of Committees thereof;`
  line
  line `(d) the pay and allowances and leave and other conditions of service of officers (other than those`
  line `appointed by the Central Government) and other employees of the Authority;`
  line
  line `(e) the maintenance of its accounts;`
  line
  line `(f) the maintenance of the registers and other records of the Authority and its various Committees;`
  line
  line `(g) the appointment by the Authority of agents to discharge on its behalf any of its functions;`
  line
  line `(h) the persons by whom, and the manner in which, payments, deposits and investments may be`
  line `made on behalf of the Authority.`
  line
  line `(3) No regulation made by the Authority shall have effect until it has been approved by the Central`
  line `Government and published in the Official Gazette, and the Central Government, in confirming a`
  line `regulation, may make any change therein which appears to it to be necessary.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, cancel any regulation which`
  line `it has confirmed and thereupon the regulation shall cease to have effect.`
  line
  line `^1[(5) Every regulation made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before`
  line `each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised`
  line `in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the regulation or both Houses agree that the regulation should not be made, the regulation shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that regulation.]`
